Chart 2: Overlap between GP and ASC data

  • Based on data pooled over the entire period
  • How to read: In Neath Port Talbot, over the entire period, 1,644 (1,584+60) people were ever identified as unpaid carers in GP records (81%) and 457 (457+60) were ever identified as unpaid carers in ASC data (21%). 60 people were identified in both types of records (3%).

Chart 4: Carers in administrative records compared to census [relative]

  • How to read: In Neath Port Talbot, over the entire period, 2,024 people were identified as unpaid carers in either GP or ASC records (GP ASC). According to the 2021 Census, there were 16,565 unpaid carers in Neath Port Talbot in March 2021. Therefore, 11% of unpaid carers in Neath Port Talbot were successfully identified in administrative records - assuming they are the one and same population.
